{
  "pack_id": "v1_alpha",
  "version": "0.4.7",
  "schema_version": 2,
  "description": "DAIMON V1 alpha bundled creature pool. 200 monsters across 6 elements (5 ring + 1 outside) and 6 archetypes. Phase 4e introduced NORMAL as the splashable utility element (15 NORMAL cards, archetype=null) and trimmed 15 generic elementals (8 vanilla commons + 4 singleton uncommons + 2 generic rares + 1 redundant REVENANT epic) to keep the total at 200. Phase 4f-pool promoted 4 epics → legendary (`magma_tyrant` L1 INFERNO, `worldroot_sentinel` L2 BULWARK, `tide_empress` L3 TIDAL, `tempest_apex` L4 STORMCHAIN) wired to the Phase 4f-engine rule-change dispatcher; tagged the 2 existing legendaries with `rule_change` (`voidking_morr` L5 REVENANT, `world_eater` L6 FLUX); migrated 5 INFERNO cards from APPLY_BURN → APPLY_BURN_STACK (lava_skink, brimling, ashpup, blazefiend, ash_strider); migrated wrought_bear from ON_TAKE_DAMAGE → ON_DAMAGE_TAKEN (post-shield-landing semantic per charter §21.2). Phase 4h (this version) closes the catalog/engine gap by binding the 3 unused Phase 4f-engine ops (THORNS, GRANT_EXTRA_ACTION, SACRIFICE_SELF) and 1 unused when (ON_EXTRA_ACTION_GRANTED, ON_HEAL_RECEIVED) to actual catalog cards via 7 in-place trigger rewrites: thornserpent + bramble_warden gain THORNS (BULWARK identity); boltrunner + shock_runner gain GRANT_EXTRA_ACTION on ON_KILL (STORMCHAIN tempo cascade — now actually consumes the L4 cap-raise); arc_lancer gains ON_EXTRA_ACTION_GRANTED → DAMAGE (extra-action receiver pattern); voidling gains ON_LOW_HP SACRIFICE_SELF (REVENANT death-engine — feeds L5 doubling); coral_augur swaps ON_TAKE_DAMAGE ADD_SHIELD → ON_HEAL_RECEIVED ADD_SHIELD (TIDAL heal-reactor pattern). Per-archetype × rarity matrix unchanged (all rewrites in-place); rarity histogram unchanged (98C/60U/28R/8E/6L); per-element unchanged (FIRE=37 NATURE=36 NORMAL=15 VOID=39 VOLT=37 WATER=36). Phase 5 (sim balance) follows.",
